0: import json# Read the ABM filewith open('abm.txt', 'r') as f:      text = f.read()# Create a dictionary to store the extracted datahousehold_variables = {}# Split the text into lineslines = text.split("\n")# Iterate through each linefor line in lines:      # Check if the line starts with "HouseHold"      if line.startswith("HouseHold"):          # Extract the name of the household          name = line.split(":")[1]          # Create a new key-value pair in the dictionary          household_variables[name] = {}          # Continue iterating until the next line          continue      # Split the line into key-value pairs      pairs = line.split(",")      # Iterate through each pair      for pair in pairs:          # Split the pair into key and value          key, value = pair.split(":")          # Add the key-value pair to the household_variables dictionary          household_variables[name][key] = {"short_description": value, "data_type": None, "initial_value": None}# Convert the dictionary to JSON formatjson_string = json.dumps(household_variables)# Print the JSON stringprint(json_string)"""
